urney-of-the-brave-300194315.html |title=From Universal Pictures Home Entertainment: The Land Before Time: Journey of the Brave |date=December 17, 2015 |accessdate=February 1, 2016 |publisher=PR Newswire |author=Universal Pictures Home Entertainment}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Range 15]]''\n| President\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Three Days in August]]''\n| John\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Bigger Fatter Liar]]''\n| Larry Wolf\n| Direct-to-video<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.kusi.com/story/34454732/from-universal-pictures-home-entertainment-ricky-garcia-and-barry-bostwick-go-head-to-head-in-the-all-new-side-splitting-comedy-bigger-fatter-liar |title=From Universal Pictures Home Entertainment: Ricky Garcia And Barry Bostwick Go Head To Head In The All-New Side-Splitting Comedy Bigger Fatter Liar |publisher=Universal Pictures Home Entertainment |via=[[KUSI]] |date=February 8, 2017 |access-date=February 9, 2017 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211075230/http://www.kusi.com/story/34454732/from-universal-pictures-home-entertainment-ricky-garcia-and-barry-bostwick-go-head-to-head-in-the-all-new-side-splitting-comedy-bigger-fatter-liar |archivedate=February 11, 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| ''[[Incredibles 2]]''\n| Mayor\n| Voice role<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/incredibles-2-review-holly-hunter-1202837069/r |title=Film Review: \u2018Incredibles 2\u2019 |publisher=Variety |date=June 11, 2018 |access-date=June 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Santa Girl''\n| Santa Claus\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| ''Grand-Daddy Day Care''\n| Dynamite Dan North\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Undercover Brother 2]]''\n| The Man\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[American Pie Presents: Girls' Rules]]''\n| PeePaw\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Murder by Natural Causes]]''\n| Gil Weston\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[You Can't Take It with You (play)#Film and TV adaptations|You Can't Take It With You]]''\n| Anthony Kirby, Jr.\n| Television film (note: filmed version of the play)\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Hawaii Five-O (1968 TV series)|Hawaii Five-O]]''\n| Lucas Sandover\n| Episode \"Year of the Horse\"\n|-\n| 1980\n| ''[[Scruples (miniseries)|Scruples]]''\n| Spider Elliot\n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''Red Flag: The Ultimate Game''\n| Maj. Jay Rivers\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1982\n| ''[[Working (musical)|Working]]'' \n| Steelworker\n| [[American Playhouse]] production\n|-\n| 1983 \n| ''Summer Girl''\n| Gavin Shelburne\n| Television film \n|-\n| 1983\n| ''An Uncommon Love'' \n| Mr. Kinser\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[George Washington (miniseries)|George Washington]]'' \n| Gen. [[George Washington]]\n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[A Woman of Substance (miniseries)|A Woman of Substance]]''\n| Major Paul McGill\n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''Deceptions''\n| Grant Roberts\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1986\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | ''[[George Washington II: The Forging of a Nation]]''\n| President [[George Washington]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''Betrayed By Innocence''\n| Nick DeLeon \n| Television film\n|-\n| 1987 \n| ''[[I'll Take Manhattan (miniseries)|I'll Take Manhattan]]''\n| Zachary Amberville\n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[War and Remembrance (miniseries)|War and Remembrance]]''\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | Lieutenant Carter \"Lady\" Aster \n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Body of Evidence (1988 film)|Body of Evidence]]''\n| Mark Dwyer\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Till We Meet Again (Judith Krantz)|Till We Meet Again]]''\n| Terrence 'Mac' McGuire\n| Television mini-series\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Parent Trap III]]\n| Jeffrey Wyatt\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Parent Trap: Hawaiian Honeymoon]]''\n| Jeffrey Wyatt\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Challenger (1990 film)|Challenger]]''\n| Comm. Francis R. Scobee\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[The Great Air Race (miniseries)|The Great Air Race]]''\n| Roscoe Turner\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[The Golden Palace]]''\n| Nick DiCarlo\n| Episode \"Just a Gigolo\"\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Once in a Lifetime (1994 film)|Once in a Lifetime]]''\n| Dr. Matthew Dane\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1996\u20132002\n| ''[[Spin City]]''\n| Mayor Randall Winston\n| Main role, 144 episodes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''A Different Kind of Christmas''\n| Frank Mallory\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Lexx]]''\n| [[Thodin]]\n| Episode \"[[List of Lexx episodes#ep1|I Worship His Shadow]]\"\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[One Hot Summer Night]]''\n| Art Brooks\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[The New Batman Adventures]]''\n| Irv Kleinman / Bernie Benson\n| Voice role, episode \"[[List of The New Batman Adventures episodes#ep13|Mean Seasons]]\"\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]''\n| Mr.Randolph\n| Episode \"[[Scrubs (season 3)#ep55|My Dirty Secret]]\"\n|-\n| 2004\u20132007\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Oliver Gates\n| Recurring role, 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Las Vegas (TV series)|Las Vegas]]''\n| Martin\n| Episode \"[[List of Las Vegas episodes#ep58|Down and Dirty]]\"\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Cold Case (TV series)|Cold Case]]''\n| Roy Brigham Anthony\n| Episode \"[[Cold Case (season 2)#ep44|Creatures of the Night]]\"\n|-\n| 2007\u20132012\n| ''[[Phineas and Ferb]]''\n| Grandpa Clyde Flynn\n| Recurring role, 12 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n| Roger Adams\n| Episodes \"[[Odor in the Court]]\", \"[[Betty Suarez Land]]\"\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''Love is a Four Letter Word''\n| Mr. Harper\n| Television film<ref>{{cite web|title=Love is a Four Letter Word {{!}} Hallmark Movies and Mysteries|url=http://www.hallmarkmoviesandmysteries.com/love-is-a-four-letter-word|website=Hallmark Movies and Mysteries|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Depth Charge''\n| President Taylor \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Holiday Baggage''\n| Pete Murphy\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Nip/Tuck]]''\n| Roger Payne\n| Episode \"[[Nip/Tuck (season 6)#ep82|Don Hoberman]]\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]''\n| The Amazing Jay\n| Episode \"[[Supernatural (season 4)#ep72|Criss Angel is a Douchebag]]\"\n|-\n| 2009\u20132010\n| ''[['Til Death]]''\n| George Von Stuessen\n| Episodes \"Eddie's Book,\" \"The Baby\"\n|- \n| 2010\u20132012\n| ''[[Cougar Town]]''\n| Roger Frank\n| Recurring role (seasons 1\u20133), 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' \n| Tim Stanwick\n| Episode \"[[The Rocky Horror Glee Show]]\" (cameo)\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Secrets of the Mountain]]''\n| Henry Beecham\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Hot in Cleveland]]'' \n| Hugh\n| Episode \"[[Hot in Cleveland (season 3)#ep55|What's Behind the Door]]\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The New Normal (TV series)|The New Normal]]\n| Marty Sawyer\n| Episode \"Pardon Me\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Scandal (TV series)|Scandal]]''\n| Fitzgerald \"Jerry\" Grant II\n| Episodes \"[[Scandal (season 2)#ep18|A Criminal, a Whore, an Idiot and a Liar]]\", \"[[Scandal (season 3)#ep36|Everything's Coming Up Mellie]]\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Haunting Of]]''\n| himself\n| Episode \"The Haunting of Barry Bostwick\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Blast Vegas]]''\n| Sal\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Masters of Sex]]''\n| Morris\n| Episode \"[[Masters of Sex (season 1)#ep6|Brave New World]]\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Teen Beach Movie]]''\n| Big Poppa\n| [[Disney Channel Original Movie]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Psych]]''\n| Roland Armitage\n| Episode \"[[Psych: The Musical]]\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Enlisted (TV series)|Enlisted]]\n| Russell\n| Episode \"Vets\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[New Girl (TV series)|New Girl]]\n| Harland Cooper\n| Episode \"[[New Girl (season 4)#ep83|LAXmas]]\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]\n| Collin Winthrop\n| Episode \"[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation (season 15)#ep335|The End Game]]\"\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| ''[[Still t